author: Heather Elicker
comment: This app has suddenly become a huge disappointment. It won't scan correctly, and has taken my last 3 deposits and put a 5 day hold on them...for no apparent reason. The telebranch said it could be 1000s of reasons why. They couldn't give me an answer. So now I have hundreds of dollars on hold until next Friday. Super frustrating. This has never happened before. Maybe if you could figure out how to take a correct scan my checks wouldn't be on hold for so long.

It now thinks I'm rooted (I'm not, though I am using LineageOS) and won't let me use the app. Even if I was rooted, why do you care? I'm allowed to do online banking on my laptop, and I have root access to that.

author: lauren giraldi
comment: I really haven't had too many problems with the app, but it's force closed a few times, is a little slow, and the whole layout looks like a jr-high student made it. I haven't received any updates for the app and I've had it for over 7 months now. I travel a lot so the mobile deposits are convenient for me and if the pictures of the checks turn out blurry, I can retake the picture and it's usually fine. Overall the whole app just really needs a facelift. It lacks professionalism and is almost "too simple" and very plain. Not really something I am impressed with at all.
